00:17:52,994 --> 00:17:57,216
and so it locks the camera there and part of that is to keep them from seeing the secret

320
00:17:57,276 --> 00:18:01,658
over on the left, but it also focuses the player on the combat and really makes that

321
00:18:01,698 --> 00:18:06,781
feel like an isolated moment. It ends up looking like this where the camera is locked horizontally

322
00:18:06,801 --> 00:18:11,864
and it just sort of like encapsulates this is its own distinct combat moment. And we

323
00:18:11,884 --> 00:18:16,106
did this sort of camera work all over the game. It ended up being a really, really important

324
00:18:16,146 --> 00:18:18,788
tool to pacing throughout the entire game.

325
00:18:20,149 --> 00:18:24,932
Another way I often use space to control combat pacing in my 3D games refers back to that

